Faulty traffic lights are not only a daily hazard but also a downright pain in the neck for Johannesburg motorists. Transport MMC, Funzela Ngobeni, wants to do something about it. He spoke with eNCA's Tumelo Mothotoane about the situation. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg will soon have a police unit dedicated to the vandalism of infrastructure. Around 120 traffic lights were damaged between December and January. READ: City Power: Cable theft and vandalism is an ongoing problem It will cost the city about R37-million to fix them. Transport MMC Funzela Ngobeni said the unit will be called Infrastructure Protection Unity under JMPD. "It's going to be on the same level as K9-unit with your land invasion unit. "We want to give proper support so that we can focus on infrastructure on vandalism. It is a big issue to the economy, we need to face it head-on and we need to put resources behind it."